254
00:17:30,041 --> 00:17:33,416
- ( sobbing )

255
00:17:41,625 --> 00:17:43,541
- I PROMISED THAT
I WOULD SHOW HER

256
00:17:43,625 --> 00:17:45,541
THE PLACE WHERE I WAS BORN.

257
00:18:22,583 --> 00:18:25,375
I TOLD HER THAT SHE SHOULD
THROW AWAY THAT THING,

258
00:18:25,458 --> 00:18:27,041
BUT BECAUSE SHE WAS AN ENGINEER,

259
00:18:27,125 --> 00:18:29,291
SHE COULDN'T BRING
HERSELF TO DO IT.

260
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:46,250
YOU KNOW, I REALLY WISH
THAT I COULD SHOW YOU

261
00:18:46,333 --> 00:18:49,291
HOW IT WAS THAT SHE WALKED.

262
00:18:49,375 --> 00:18:50,958
IT WAS TRULY BEAUTIFUL.

263
00:18:53,125 --> 00:18:54,083
BUT THEN...

264
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:58,416
WE ARRIVED AT MY BIRTHPLACE

265
00:18:58,500 --> 00:19:01,708
TO DISCOVER THAT IT HAD
BECOME A WASTELAND.

266
00:19:01,791 --> 00:19:03,833
BUT MARTHA WAS
CAPTIVATED BY THE PLACE.

267
00:19:25,916 --> 00:19:28,541
AND SO, I BUILT A HOUSE HERE.

268
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:30,791
AND DID EVERYTHING JUST LIKE
MARTHA TOLD ME TO.

269
00:19:30,875 --> 00:19:34,125
I CULTIVATED, PLANTED FLOWERS
AND BUILT A LIFE.

270
00:19:34,208 --> 00:19:36,250
THAT'S ALL THERE IS TO IT.

271
00:19:36,333 --> 00:19:38,083
- BUT ISN'T IT
DIFFICULT FOR YOU?

272
00:19:38,166 --> 00:19:40,333
